state.unicode: Menelaus gains access to units from his allies' rosters for recruitment into his own. Available units from each faction are shown below. Each faction's strongest units are always displayed, but they will only become available when the allied faction unlocks them.

uientry.unicode: Reset faction groups||Group into allied factions or other factions
Click to select, double-click to initiate diplomacy

state.unicode: You have no allies who can offer units to your cause. Strike a defensive or military alliance with a faction to gain access to their unit roster.
There are no other known factions with whom you can forge an alliance at this time.

uientry.unicode: Kills||The number of kills this unit has made in this battle. Kills will count toward a unit's XP.
Unit Experience||The higher a unit's rank, the more effective they will be in battle.
XP progress||This is the unit's progress towards gaining the next XP rank.
Upkeep||This amount will be deducted from your {{tr:icon_treasury}}{{tr:treasury}} each turn while this unit exists.

state.unicode: Entity & unit size||This is a unit of large entities.||This displays the current unit size compared to the maximum unit size. Units will replenish over time when in owned territory, or when in certain stances.

Entity & unit size||This is a unit of small entities.||This displays the current unit size compared to the maximum unit size. Units will replenish over time when in owned territory, or when in certain stances.

uientry.unicode: These units are available in your Call to Arms recruitment pool. Greyed-out units are the strongest a faction can offer but are yet to unlock.\n\nOnly the proud warriors of the Amazons would refuse to answer the Call to Arms.
